{"cursor":"5908","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox Weapon| |is_ranged=yes| |image= |caption= |name=Pistolet Mitrailleur\nde 7,65mm MAS modÃ¨le 38 |type=Submachine gun |origin= France |design_date=1938\n|production_date=1939â1946 |service=1939â1950 |used_by=See Users |wars=World War\nII First Indochina War |spec_type=MAS 38 |caliber=7.65mm |part_length=224 mm\n(8.82 in) |cartridge=7.65mm Longue 7.65Ã17mm Browning SR |feed=32-round\ndetachable box magazine |action=Blowback |rate=600â700 rounds/min |velocity=350\nm/s (1,148 ft/s) |weight=2.87 kg (without magazine) 3.56 kg (with magazine)\n|length=623 mm (24.53 in) |range=100m [http://armesfrancaises.free.fr/PM%20Mle%2038.html\narmesfrancaises.free.fr] |max_range=200m }}\n\nThe 'MAS-38' was a French submachine gun designed prior to the Second World War\nand used by French and German forces. It derived from a small arms development\nprogram that took place between 1918 and 1922 under the control of the Service\nTechnique de l'Armement. A submachine gun, a light machine gun and a semi\nautomatic rifle were developed to replace all the existing small arms. Budgetary\nconstraints due to choices like building the Maginot Line led to the delay of\nadoption of these new arms except for the LMG 1924.\n","linknr":189,"url":"MAS-38","recorded":1375090441,"links":["/w/index.php?title=MAS-38&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=MAS-38&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang